data.enText: for job/course

data.chText: 申请；请求；申请书；申请表
data.enText: a formal (often written) request for sth, such as a job, permission to do sth or a place at a college or university
a planning/passport application

data.chText: 他向法庭申请保释遭到拒绝。
data.enText: His application to the court for bail has been refused.

data.chText: 会籍 / 贷款 / 执照申请
data.enText: an application for membership/a loan/a licence
an application form (= a piece of paper on which to apply for sth)

data.chText: 申请书请交校长，届时将提供详情。
data.enText: Further information is available on application to the principal.
practical use

data.chText: （尤指理论、发现等的）应用，运用
data.enText: the practical use of sth, especially a theory, discovery, etc.

data.chText: 新技术在教学上的应用
data.enText: the application of new technology to teaching

data.chText: 这项发明会在工业中得到广泛应用。
data.enText: The invention would have wide application/a wide range of applications in industry.
of paint/cream
an act of putting or spreading sth, such as paint or medical creams, onto sth else
lotion for external application only (= to be put on the skin, not swallowed)

data.chText: 刷了三道油漆才盖住了涂鸦。
data.enText: It took three applications of paint to cover the graffiti.
of rule/law
the act of making a rule, etc. operate or become effective
strict application of the law
computing
a program designed to do a particular job; a piece of software
a database application
hard work
determination to work hard at sth; great effort

data.chText: 作家要成功就得悉力以赴。
data.enText: Success as a writer demands great application.

ex.chText: 海啸发生后，该国紧急请求提供国际援助。
ex.enText: That country made an urgent request for international aid after the tsunami happened.

ex.chText: 反对党领导人再次要求他们尽快公布选举结果。
ex.enText: The opposition leader repeated his request that they release the election results as soon as possible.

synonyms.bx: 指礼貌而正式的请求，但无把握能否会得到满足。

ex.chText: 他很郁闷，因为他的申请已被拒绝。
ex.enText: He was upset because his application had been rejected.

ex.chText: 别忘了寄出你的申请表。
ex.enText: Don't forget to send off your application form.

synonyms.bx: 指以书面形式提出的请求。

tr: the action of putting something into operation
example: the application of indexes to tables of data
it is a job requiring serious application
the doctor prescribed a topical application of iodine
a complete bleach requires several applications
the surface was ready for a coating of paint

tr: the act of bringing something to bear
using it for a particular purpose
example: he advocated the application of statistics to the problem
a novel application of electronics to medical diagnosis

tr: liquid preparation having a soothing or antiseptic or medicinal action when applied to the skin
a verbal or written request for assistance or employment or admission to a school
example: December 31 is the deadline for applications

tr: a program that gives a computer instructions that provide the user with tools to accomplish a task
example: he has tried several different word processing applications

value.def: An application for something such as a job or membership of an organization is a formal written request for it.

example.ex: His application for membership of the organisation was rejected...
example.tran: 他想要加入该组织的申请遭到了拒绝。

example.ex: ...Turkey's application to join the European Community...
example.tran: 土耳其要求加入欧共体的申请

example.ex: Applications should be submitted as early as possible...

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>for</l> n, N to-inf, also <l>on/upon</l> N

value.tran: 申请；请求；申请书；申请表

value.def: The application of a rule or piece of knowledge is the use of it in a particular situation.

example.ex: Students learned the practical application of the theory they had learned in the classroom...
example.tran: 学生们学会了将课堂上学到的理论付诸实际应用。

example.ex: Simon's book provides a succinct outline of artificial intelligence and its application to robotics.
example.tran: 西蒙的书简明扼要地概括了人工智能及其在机器人技术方面的应用。

value.def: In computing, an application is a piece of software designed to carry out a particular task.
Application is hard work and concentration on what you are doing over a period of time.

example.ex: ...his immense talent, boundless energy and unremitting application.
example.tran: 他横溢的才华、充沛的精力和不懈的努力

value.def: The application of something to a surface is the act or process of putting it on or rubbing it into the surface.

example.ex: With repeated applications of weedkiller, the weeds were overcome.
example.tran: 经过反复施用除草剂，杂草得以彻底根除。
